Incident Response > [T1]: Understanding Key Concepts: Attack/Threat Vectors

Attack/Threat Vectors

Attack vectors refer to the route that attackers take to infiltrate your organization. In other words, a way for attackers to enter a network or system. Social engineering, phishing emails, insider threats, and exploiting web vulnerabilities are popular attack vectors. The Top Attack Vectors report by expel, released in February 2022, suggested that phishing is the most used attack vector.

 

Attackers will not stop targeting your organization; preparing in advance so you can respond quickly and effectively is a wise decision. Incident response's primary goals are allowing you to respond systematically by following predefined steps, minimizing attack damage, and utilizing past incidents to improve your ability to respond to future incidents.
